---
title: Hoisin Steak Supreme with Snow Peas, Edamame, and Scallion Mashed Potatoes
description: This may be a steak-and-potatoes recipe, but it probably isn’t like one you’ve tried before. It starts out with beef sirloin and a creamy mash, but then takes a detour to the east with some daring Asian flavors. The meat gets drizzled with a sauce sweetened with hoisin, while the spuds are studded with scallions. And the veggies are a double treat with sweet snow peas and edamame soy beans. For those who like it spicy, there’s even a drizzle of sriracha to finish.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hoisin-steak-effc96d0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hoisin-steak-5b76e49230006c090e4af622-558ec613.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 990 kcal
  fat: 62 g
  saturated fat: 25 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1450 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-steak-supreme-5b76e49230006c090e4af622
cuisine: Asian
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and
whites. Set aside. Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes and place in a
#medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil over
high heat. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain well.

Return empty #pot{} to stove over low heat. Add @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} and
half the scallion whites. Let butter melt and scallion whites soften, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Return potatoes to pot and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in
@sour cream{4%tablespoon} and half the scallion greens. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Keep covered on stove over low heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}
over medium-high heat. Pat @sirloin steak{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}; season with
plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness,
~{4-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside on a #plate{} to rest.

In a second large pan, heat @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} over medium-high heat. Add
@snow peas{8%ounce} and @edamame{4%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook,
tossing, until snow peas are bright green and edamame is lightly charred,
~{3-4%minutes}. Toss in half the @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wash out any blackened bits in pan used for steak; dry well. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining scallion
whites and cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @soy sauce{2%tablespoon},
@beef demi-glace{1}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, and 2 TBSP water. Bring to a simmer
and let reduce slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reduce heat to low, then stir in
@butter{1%tablespoon}. Stir in any juices released by steak, then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide potatoes, snow peas, and edamame between plates. Slice steak against the grain
and arrange next to potatoes. Spoon sauce over steak, then garnish with remaining
scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Drizzle with @sriracha{1%teaspoon}
to taste.

> This may be a steak-and-potatoes recipe, but it probably isn't like one you've tried
